      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "~Concept \\~0~ See https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18246#issuecomment-623046686\r\n\r\nPros of the current implementation (from [Qt docs](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/designer-using-a-ui-file.html#widgets-and-dialogs-with-auto-connect)):\r\n> Automatic connection of signals and slots provides both a standard naming convention and an explicit interface for widget designers to work to. By providing source code that implements a given interface, user interface designers can check that their designs actually work without having to write code themselves.\r\n\r\nOTOH, `QMetaObject::connectSlotsByName()` generates the old syntax (see: [QTBUG-76375](https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-76375)).\r\n\r\nI'd prefer to handle ui-form-emitted signals in a distinguishable way, and to have 100% test coverage for them. So I'm ok with auto-connection for such cases.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nHere are some refs for the record:\r\n- [Using a Designer UI File - Automatic Connections](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/designer-using-a-ui-file.html#automatic-connections)\r\n- [`QObject` Class - Auto-Connection](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qobject.html#auto-connection)\r\n- [`QMetaObject::connectSlotsByName()`](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qmetaobject.html#connectSlotsByName)\r\n- [QTBUG-76375](https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-76375)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n@promag \r\n> ... this is still incomplete.\r\n\r\nMind adding \"WIP\" marker?",
      "created_at" : "2020-03-03T10:16:08Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18246#issuecomment-593872532",
      "id" : 593872532,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/18246",
